race.comment: A good contest. MYTEMPTATION (5) was just nudged out at The Valley as favourite and will be fitter again. Should enjoy a soft run and is a decent winning chance. Hayes-trained LE FERRARI (6) peaks off three solid metro outings and is well placed to win. Maps for the run of the race and it's hard to risk the yard. A solid each-way play. MODOWN (4) resumes owning two wins at the jumpouts. Has the rail and is talented. A bold return is on the cards. CAPPER THIRTYNINE (7) comes out of the MYTEMPTATION race when narrowly beaten. Meech rides today and will go forward. Just needs average luck to be in the finish. VERDAD (3) resumes and performs fresh. He also deserves consideration.
